# State Management Guide

## Provider Types

| Provider | Use Case | Example |
|----------|----------|---------|
| `StateNotifierProvider` | Complex state with business logic | Auth, Dashboard |
| `Provider` | Dependencies, services | Repositories, Use Cases |
| `StateProvider` | Simple mutable state (use sparingly) | Selected filter |
| `FutureProvider` | Async data without manual refresh | Config data |

---

## Base Classes

### For Non-Paginated Features: `BaseNotifier<T>`

```dart
class DashboardNotifier extends BaseNotifier<Dashboard> {
  final GetDashboardUseCase _useCase;
  
  DashboardNotifier(this._useCase) : super();
  
  @override
  Future<Result<Dashboard>> fetchData({Map<String, dynamic>? params}) async {
    return await _useCase.execute(
      statsType: params?['statsType'] as String?,
    );
  }
  
  // Convenience method with typed parameters
  Future<void> loadDashboard({String? statsType}) async {
    return load(params: {'statsType': statsType});
  }
}

final dashboardProvider = StateNotifierProvider<DashboardNotifier, BaseState<Dashboard>>((ref) {
  final useCase = ref.watch(getDashboardUseCaseProvider);
  return DashboardNotifier(useCase);
});
```

### For Paginated Features: `PaginatedNotifier<T>`

```dart
class NotificationNotifier extends PaginatedNotifier<Notification> {
  final GetNotificationsUseCase _useCase;
  
  NotificationNotifier(this._useCase) : super();

  @override
  Future<Result<PaginatedList<Notification>>> fetchPage({
    required int page,
    Map<String, dynamic>? params,
  }) async {
    return await _useCase.execute(
      page: page,
      read: params?['read'] as String?,
    );
  }
  
  Future<void> loadNotifications({String? read}) async {
    return load(params: {'read': read});
  }
  
  Future<void> loadMoreNotifications({String? read}) async {
    return loadMore(params: {'read': read});
  }
}

final notificationProvider = StateNotifierProvider<NotificationNotifier, PaginatedState<Notification>>((ref) {
  final useCase = ref.watch(getNotificationsUseCaseProvider);
  return NotificationNotifier(useCase);
});
```

