## State Classes (Freezed)

### Non-Paginated State

Use `BaseState<T>` from `core/presentation/providers/base_state.dart`:

```dart
// States available:
BaseState.initial()
BaseState.loading()
BaseState.loaded(T data)
BaseState.error(String message)
```

### Custom State with Operations (e.g., Profile)

For features with update operations, add updating/updated states:

```dart
@freezed
class ProfileState with _$ProfileState {
  const factory ProfileState.initial() = _Initial;
  const factory ProfileState.loading() = _Loading;
  const factory ProfileState.loaded(Profile profile) = _Loaded;
  const factory ProfileState.updating(Profile profile) = _Updating;  // Show loading while keeping data
  const factory ProfileState.updated(Profile profile) = _Updated;    // Success feedback
  const factory ProfileState.error(String message, {Profile? profile}) = _Error;  // Keep data on error
}
```

Or create custom state:

```dart
@freezed
class AuthState with _$AuthState {
  const factory AuthState.initial() = _Initial;
  const factory AuthState.loading() = _Loading;
  const factory AuthState.authenticated(User user) = _Authenticated;
  const factory AuthState.unauthenticated() = _Unauthenticated;
  const factory AuthState.error(String message) = _Error;
}
```

### Paginated State

Use `PaginatedState<T>` from `core/presentation/providers/paginated_state.dart`:

```dart
// States available:
PaginatedState.initial()
PaginatedState.loading()
PaginatedState.loaded(PaginatedList<T> data)
PaginatedState.loadingMore(PaginatedList<T> data)  // Infinite scroll
PaginatedState.error(String message)
```

