## Result Pattern

Located in `core/domain/result.dart`:

```dart
sealed class Result<T> {}
final class Success<T> extends Result<T> { final T data; }
final class Failure<T> extends Result<T> { 
  final String message;
  final String? code;
  final Map<String, dynamic>? data;
}
```

### Extension Methods Available

```dart
// Fold into single value
result.fold(
  onSuccess: (success) => handleData(success.data),
  onFailure: (failure) => handleError(failure.message),
);

// Map success to another type
Result<UserDto> dtoResult = ...;
Result<User> domainResult = dtoResult.map((dto) => dto.toDomain());

// Quick accessors
result.dataOrNull      // T? - data if success, null if failure
result.failureMessage  // String? - message if failure, null if success
result.isSuccess       // bool
result.isFailure       // bool
```

### Usage in Use Cases

```dart
Future<Result<User>> execute(String email, String password) async {
  try {
    final user = await _repository.login(email, password);
    return Success(user);
  } on NetworkException catch (e) {
    return Failure(message: e.message, code: 'NETWORK_ERROR');
  } catch (e) {
    return Failure(message: e.toString());
  }
}
```

### Usage in Notifiers

```dart
Future<void> login(String email, String password) async {
  state = const AuthState.loading();
  final result = await _useCase.execute(email, password);
  
  switch (result) {
    case Success<User>(:final data):
      state = AuthState.authenticated(data);
    case Failure<User>(:final message):
      state = AuthState.error(message);
  }
}
```

