## Provider Organization

### Standard Pattern (Post-Login Features)

Use this pattern for all features that are accessed after user login:

```dart
// 1. Service provider (FutureProvider - only async part)
final dashboardServiceProvider = FutureProvider<DashboardService>((ref) async {
  final client = await ref.watch(apiClientProvider.future);
  return client.getService<DashboardService>();
});

// 2. Repository provider (uses .requireValue)
final dashboardRepositoryProvider = Provider<DashboardRepository>((ref) {
  final service = ref.watch(dashboardServiceProvider).requireValue;
  return DashboardRepository(service);
});

// 3. Use case provider
final getDashboardUseCaseProvider = Provider<GetDashboardUseCase>((ref) {
  final repository = ref.watch(dashboardRepositoryProvider);
  return GetDashboardUseCase(repository);
});

// 4. Notifier provider (receives use case directly)
final dashboardProvider = StateNotifierProvider<DashboardNotifier, BaseState<Dashboard>>((ref) {
  final useCase = ref.watch(getDashboardUseCaseProvider);
  return DashboardNotifier(useCase);
});
```

### Notifier with Direct Dependencies (Recommended)

```dart
class DashboardNotifier extends BaseNotifier<Dashboard> {
  final GetDashboardUseCase _getDashboardUseCase;

  DashboardNotifier(this._getDashboardUseCase) : super();

  @override
  Future<Result<Dashboard>> fetchData({Map<String, dynamic>? params}) async {
    return await _getDashboardUseCase.execute(...);
  }
}
```

### Auth-Dependent Pattern (Pre-Login Features)

Use `Ref` pattern only for features that need to handle async initialization errors (e.g., auth):

```dart
class AuthNotifier extends StateNotifier<AuthState> {
  final Ref _ref;

  AuthNotifier(this._ref) : super(const AuthState.initial());

  Future<void> login(...) async {
    try {
      // Access providers lazily - they may not be ready
      final useCase = await _ref.read(loginUseCaseProvider.future);
      final result = await useCase.execute(...);
    } catch (e) {
      state = AuthState.error('Failed: $e');
    }
  }
}
```

### When to Use Each Pattern

| Pattern | When to Use |
|---------|-------------|
| **FutureProvider chain** | Features loaded immediately after login (Dashboard, first screens) |
| `.requireValue` | Features accessed later when services are guaranteed ready (lazy screens) |
| `Ref` + `.future` | Auth flows or when service initialization timing is uncertain |

**⚠️ IMPORTANT:** `.requireValue` throws `StateError` if `FutureProvider` is still loading!
Only use it when you are 100% certain the provider has already resolved.

